The paper proposes a method for generating realistic sonar data, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as generative adversarial networks (GANs) and image synthesis. The application domain is autonomous underwater vehicles (RO), and the paper discusses the use of the generated data for tuning and validation of autonomous target recognition (ATR) systems (AI). The paper also mentions the control over the topography of the generated data, which suggests the use of graphics (GR) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the quantitative assessment of the generated data, which suggests the use of machine learning (LG) techniques.
